Musselroe Wind Farm is connected to the greater NEM network by a long radial transmission line extending from Launceston. This line is less than 100kV, and is removed in the network construction phase, causing the wind farm to be located more than 50km from its nearest node. Tamar Valley is located near the start of this long-radial line, and is reasonable to assume that generated at Musselroe would be injected into Tamar Valley. Consequently, while a GA entry for Musselroe does exist, Tamar Valley has been assigned instead.
